                            <comment id="13678934" author="lhofhansl" created="Sun, 9 Jun 2013 03:58:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This a good idea. Which versions HDFS support this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13679712" author="blackpearl" created="Mon, 10 Jun 2013 18:08:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lhofhansl&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lhofhansl&quot;&gt;Lars Hofhansl&lt;/a&gt;I&apos;m not sure if any Apache version of HDFS supports this. This is supported in Facebook&apos;s version of HDFS. You can find the code on github here : &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/facebook/hadoop-20&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/facebook/hadoop-20&lt;/a&gt; and here is an example of where it is used : &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/facebook/hadoop-20/blob/master/src/hdfs/org/apache/hadoop/hdfs/server/datanode/BlockInlineChecksumWriter.java#L306&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/facebook/hadoop-20/blob/master/src/hdfs/org/apache/hadoop/hdfs/server/datanode/BlockInlineChecksumWriter.java#L306&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13679750" author="lhofhansl" created="Mon, 10 Jun 2013 18:34:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This sounds similar &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-2465&quot; title=&quot;Add HDFS support for fadvise readahead and drop-behind&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HDFS-2465&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HDFS-2465&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (dfs.datanode.sync.behind.writes option).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
